{"TopicId":39573,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Strengths of the reaction wheel system","CreatedByName":"Levelord","CreatedById":57711,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T02:42:49Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Levelord","CreatedById":57711,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T02:42:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIf you have not realized, the new Inline reaction wheel system coupled with the pre-installed SAS system in probes, makes for very stable and recoverable rovers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn fact, the reactions wheels are so strong, they are able to maintain stable and strong wheelies for rovers up to at least 20m/s without flipping.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/6R9O2N4.png\u0022 alt=\u00226R9O2N4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/EhPNWYX.png\u0022 alt=\u0022EhPNWYX.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs an added bonus, the system now gives probe bodies enough torque to literally flip itself in the air back onto it\u0027s wheels. Working in Kerbin gravity shows how powerful it is, and I\u0027m now convinced that it should be a mandatory design feature of every rover I make.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AvXv4UT.png\u0022 alt=\u0022AvXv4UT.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/C9egBoJ.png\u0022 alt=\u0022C9egBoJ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-07-28T20:07:38Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2013 08:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Levelord\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"spikeyhat09","CreatedById":39217,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T02:55:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethe less rigidness of the new system means you cant walk away or play another game while your rocket does a 30 minute burn.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Doctor Lag","CreatedById":23856,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T03:09:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022spikeyhat09\u0022 data-cite=\u0022spikeyhat09\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Ethe less rigidness of the new system means you cant walk away or play another game while your rocket does a 30 minute burn.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELearn to build a rocket?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn topic, thanks for the info - I\u0027ve been working on a new rover and I\u0027ll use this. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Accelerando","CreatedById":543,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T03:19:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Doctor Lag\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Doctor Lag\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ELearn to build a rocket?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPointless condescending remark posed in reaction to similar?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbol Prime","CreatedById":57626,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T03:22:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve been able to make a semi working unicycle with the new sas. You need to tend to it constantly however.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SuperWeegee4000","CreatedById":71621,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T17:49:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EImages don\u0027t show.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Levelord","CreatedById":57711,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T20:18:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SuperWeegee4000\u0022 data-cite=\u0022SuperWeegee4000\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EImages don\u0027t show.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFix\u0027d. Hope it works now \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T20:24:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFew days ago I build a unicycle. I haven\u0027t tested it in low gravity but around KSC it works reasonably well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://tex.texel.com/ksp021/screenshot1.png\u0022 alt=\u0022screenshot1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECheck out what XaTriX did. SAS Breakdancing.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/K6EQwIAPhnU?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-07-28T20:26:46Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2013 08:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Tex_NL\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"M83","CreatedById":68926,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T20:48:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027m a big supporter of the reaction wheel system. Some rockets that are absolutely huge now are a lot more stable, which saves time and fuel since I don\u0027t have to work on corrections or anything like that.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anton P. Nym","CreatedById":73533,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T20:59:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EFew days ago I build a unicycle. I haven\u0027t tested it in low gravity but around KSC it works reasonably well.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESomewhere, out there, a Borderlands fan is about to recreate \u003Ca href=\u0022http://borderlands.wikia.com/wiki/Claptrap?file=Claptrap.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EClaptrap\u003C/a\u003E in KSP... (\u003Ca href=\u0022https://soundcloud.com/xbox/nar-live-claptrap-8d-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis soundclip in particular\u003C/a\u003E applies....)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E -- Steve\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-28T21:10:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anton P. Nym\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Anton P. Nym\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ESomewhere, out there, a Borderlands fan is about to recreate \u003Ca href=\u0022http://borderlands.wikia.com/wiki/Claptrap?file=Claptrap.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EClaptrap\u003C/a\u003E in KSP... (\u003Ca href=\u0022https://soundcloud.com/xbox/nar-live-claptrap-8d-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis soundclip in particular\u003C/a\u003E applies....)\u003Cp\u003E -- Steve\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESeriously, I haven\u0027t got a clue what you\u0027re talking about.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}